{
  "name": "RPlog_Liza_s_Morning_After",
  "title": "Liza's Morning After",
  "summary": "Hungover and miserable after a night of revelry, the young pilot Liza wakes in the captain's quarters of the pirate Juran's ship to find him cheerfully singing sea shanties and entirely unsympathetic to her suffering. Juran bullies and teases her through her nausea, refusing to let her sleep it off and insisting she join him for some flying instead. He hauls her out through the airlock and into a fighter for an impromptu dogfight in space over Tatooine, his astromech and her own struggling ship trading fire and dodges. Despite Liza's protests that piloting isn't really her job, Juran coaches her gruffly through evasive maneuvers and grudgingly praises her progress. The lesson ends with the irascible pirate parking his fighter and declaring he never did like Tatooine, the morning after transformed into a rough but oddly affectionate flying tutorial.",
